277
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,160
Oh, I forgot to introduce myself.

278
00:13:48,160 --> 00:13:52,160
My name is Keerati. I'm new here.

279
00:13:52,680 --> 00:13:56,680
Could you all root for me?

280
00:13:57,160 --> 00:14:00,440
Wow, you're so adorable. Let's be friends.

281
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,560
No.

282
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:02,120
What?

283
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,280
I don't want to be your friend.

284
00:14:04,280 --> 00:14:07,560
The only reason I'm here is because I want to be a school queen.

285
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:11,080
And now, I am the school queen.

286
00:14:11,080 --> 00:14:13,200
You're not the school queen anymore.

287
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,960
Hey, that's not right.

288
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:17,000
Other people must vote for you to be the school queen.

289
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,520
You can't just say that you're one.

290
00:14:18,520 --> 00:14:20,400
Of course, I can. I'm prettier than you.

291
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,520
What's your problem?

292
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:23,360
That's not okay.

293
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:26,560
Let others vote for you.

294
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,000
Let me go.

295
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,080
That's really not okay.

296
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,840
I told you to let me go.

297
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:36,000
Ah, what's that?

298
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:38,360
Oh, no, lice?

299
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:40,320
Eww, why do you have lice?

300
00:14:40,320 --> 00:14:42,000
How could you be a school queen?

301
00:14:42,000 --> 00:14:44,120
Are you a lice queen?

302
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:45,520
No, no, I'm not.

303
00:14:45,520 --> 00:14:49,040
My mom will help me with that. I'll recover.

304
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:51,040
No, eww, you're a lice queen.

305
00:14:51,040 --> 00:14:53,120
Lice queen! Lice queen! Lice queen!

306
00:14:53,120 --> 00:14:54,920
Stop it!

307
00:14:54,920 --> 00:14:56,280
Lice queen! Lice queen!

308
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:57,800
Wait, it will be gone. Stop it!

309
00:14:57,800 --> 00:15:01,800
No, stop it!

310
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:06,600
Oh, Mint! Mint!

311
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:09,080
Porn, calm down. Calm!

312
00:15:09,080 --> 00:15:09,440
Mint.

313
00:15:09,440 --> 00:15:10,640
I'll get you some water!

314
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:11,640
Mint!

315
00:15:21,960 --> 00:15:24,640
I was a school queen for five years.

316
00:15:24,640 --> 00:15:26,680
She got to the school as a senior.

317
00:15:26,680 --> 00:15:28,160
And I became a lice queen.

318
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:31,440
She had lice too, actually!

319
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:32,720
I was patient.

320
00:15:32,720 --> 00:15:34,280
I put up with everything until I graduated.

321
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:37,840
I thought it would all end after I got into uni.

322
00:15:37,840 --> 00:15:39,840
But no, she's still lurking in my life like a damn ghost.

323
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:46,800
You said you’d be a cheerleader, right?

324
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:49,600
Why are you dressed like a joke-leader now?

325
00:15:49,600 --> 00:15:52,480
I don’t know! The seniors said all the positions were full.

326
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:55,200
So they gave me this costume.

327
00:15:55,200 --> 00:15:57,760
There must’ve been a mistake!

328
00:15:57,760 --> 00:16:00,080
Let’s go ask the seniors!

329
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:03,520
Let's go!

330
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:04,360
Hey!

331
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,840
No need to waste time, sweetie.

332
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:09,280
The cheerleader slots are all taken.

333
00:16:09,280 --> 00:16:10,960
You go to this uni too?

334
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:12,680
Yes, I just got here.

335
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:15,160
I wanted to join the squad, so I signed up.

336
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:19,160
Wow! But that frog suit really suits you.

337
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:22,760
Wait, don’t tell me you stole my spot?

338
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:25,320
Can’t help it if I’m simply better.

339
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:28,520
Hey! Go tell the seniors now. This is not okay!

340
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:29,800
Cheer team, ready?

341
00:16:29,800 --> 00:16:31,120
Three, four...

342
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:34,240
Grilled chicken on fire, grilled chicken on fire!

343
00:16:34,240 --> 00:16:38,200
It will be skewered!

344
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,200
Skewered from the left!

345
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:40,800
Skewered from the right!

346
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:44,440
So hot! So hot! So hot!

347
00:16:44,440 --> 00:16:46,440
Oh!

348
00:16:48,040 --> 00:16:49,880
Wait, what are you doing, frog girl?

349
00:16:49,880 --> 00:16:51,880
First you had lice, now you’re a damn frog?

350
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:54,800
How could you do this to me?

351
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,960
Calm down.

352
00:16:57,960 --> 00:16:59,600
Oh! Look! A frog attack!

353
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,600
Chill, girls!

354
00:17:03,680 --> 00:17:04,680
Stop it!

355
00:17:04,840 --> 00:17:07,120
After that grilled chicken cheer song incident at the university,

356
00:17:07,120 --> 00:17:10,120
Mint, my one and only friend, started drifting away from me.

357
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:13,240
I ended up alone.

358
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,360
Eating alone.

359
00:17:14,360 --> 00:17:17,360
Wandering around the cafeteria like a ghost with nowhere to go.

360
00:17:17,360 --> 00:17:18,600
But I endured it.

361
00:17:18,600 --> 00:17:20,360
Until the day I graduate.

362
00:17:20,360 --> 00:17:22,360
Madam...

363
00:17:22,360 --> 00:17:24,520
Still, I had my dream.

364
00:17:24,520 --> 00:17:26,320
I wanted to be a flight attendant.

365
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:30,280
But that girl, she cut in front of me, stole my spotlight,

366
00:17:30,280 --> 00:17:32,600
and crushed my dream...

367
00:17:32,600 --> 00:17:34,800
like it was just a piece of A4 paper.

368
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,400
And what did you do?

369
00:17:36,400 --> 00:17:38,120
The last time we met...

370
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:41,000
I really thought I had the upper hand.

371
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:44,760
But she nailed my coffin shut, tighter than ever.

372
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,760
That night.

373
00:17:45,760 --> 00:17:46,560
That day.

374
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:47,560
That flight...

375
00:17:57,320 --> 00:17:59,600
Well, well, look who it is.

376
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:02,280
It’s you.

377
00:18:02,280 --> 00:18:06,280
Oh? So you’re a flight attendant now? Looks nice.

378
00:18:07,560 --> 00:18:09,040
Aren't I pretty?

379
00:18:09,040 --> 00:18:13,040
But…what do you do again? Or are you...

380
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:16,800
unemployed?

381
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:19,360
That's none of your business.

382
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:21,640
Since you’re here, make yourself useful.

383
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:24,720
Put my bag in the overhead bin for me.

384
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:26,720
Certainly, ma'am.

385
00:18:30,680 --> 00:18:31,680
Step aside.

386
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:36,160
Oh, no.

387
00:18:39,600 --> 00:18:41,080
I'm sorry.

388
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:45,040
You see, I've been lifting bags all day.

389
00:18:45,040 --> 00:18:48,040
I feel so sorry for you. Let me help you.

390
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:54,640
Thank you.

391
00:18:54,640 --> 00:18:58,640
By the way, flight attendants aren’t actually required to lift passengers’ bags.

392
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:11,560
Thank you.

393
00:19:27,720 --> 00:19:29,720
Would you like tea or coffee?

394
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:35,400
Would you care for some tea or coffee?

395
00:19:38,360 --> 00:19:40,360
Tea or coffee?

396
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
Watch your tone.

397
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:47,600
Were you raised in a cave without sunlight?

398
00:19:47,600 --> 00:19:49,240
Oh, I thought you were hard of hearing.

399
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,480
You didn't answer when I asked.

400
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:52,120
So, what's it gonna be? Tea or coffee?

401
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:53,760
Can’t you speak more politely?

402
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:56,160
You're in customer service.

403
00:19:56,160 --> 00:19:58,240
I have the heart to serve…

404
00:19:58,240 --> 00:19:59,800
But I get to choose who I serve.

405
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:00,800
Wow.

406
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:05,280
That attitude came out real fast.

407
00:20:05,280 --> 00:20:07,200
Seriously...

408
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:09,520
do you really think I wanted to be a flight attendant because I love serving people?

409
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:11,600
No.

410
00:20:11,600 --> 00:20:13,800
The real reason I wanted to be a flight attendant…

411
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:15,800
was to beat you.

412
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:17,880
What do you mean?

413
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:21,400
I heard how desperately you wanted this job.

414
00:20:21,400 --> 00:20:23,400
So I went straight to the airline owner…

415
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,040
and I told him:

416
00:20:25,040 --> 00:20:27,160
“If I have to sleep with someone for this,

417
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:29,640
I better become a damn flight attendant.”

418
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:31,640
And guess what, I became a flight attendant.

419
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:36,840
Nothing in this world is more satisfying than taking you down.

420
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,200
If you want to be something,

421
00:20:38,200 --> 00:20:39,520
I’ll become it first.

422
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:40,560
If you want to be number one,

423
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:41,920
I’ll make sure I’m zero…

424
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:43,920
so you’ll never win.

425
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:45,960
I'm evil laughing now.

426
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:52,400
I still remember.

427
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,800
She once told me…

428
00:20:53,800 --> 00:20:56,560
"A girl like you will never fly high."

429
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:59,920
Well guess what? She’s now just an ex-flight attendant.

430
00:20:59,920 --> 00:21:03,920
And I own the airline.

431
00:21:04,160 --> 00:21:05,560
Don't worry, Madam.

432
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,400
f there’s anything you need me to do, just say it.

433
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:10,080
If you tell me to jump, I’ll ask how high.

434
00:21:10,080 --> 00:21:13,240
If you want me to dive, I’ll ask how deep.

435
00:21:13,240 --> 00:21:14,840
I’ve got your back.

436
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:17,600
Thank you so much, Siri.

437
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:19,680
That's the nicest thing you've said to me.

438
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,880
But I gotta thank her too.

439
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:25,880
Because of her, I became this strong.

440
00:21:27,240 --> 00:21:31,240
Ouch… ooh…

441
00:21:34,040 --> 00:21:34,960
My scalp’s so itchy.

442
00:21:34,960 --> 00:21:38,960
Could it be… lice? Maybe from a certain passenger?

443
00:21:41,720 --> 00:21:47,720
There’s a weird, musty smell lingering here.

444
00:21:49,400 --> 00:21:52,800
Hmm… musty?

445
00:21:52,800 --> 00:21:54,360
Or… must be misfortune.

446
00:21:54,360 --> 00:21:55,960
Or maybe…an aura of decay.

447
00:21:55,960 --> 00:21:59,920
A fallen socialite, perhaps?

448
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,000
Who do you think you’re talking about?

449
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:01,840
Who could that be?

450
00:22:01,840 --> 00:22:02,720
Huh?

451
00:22:02,720 --> 00:22:05,080
The stench is overwhelming.

452
00:22:05,080 --> 00:22:07,040
Better get back to your seat...

453
00:22:07,040 --> 00:22:11,040
before the smell spreads through the cabin.

454
00:22:15,280 --> 00:22:16,560
Hey!

455
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:18,640
They are both terrifying.

456
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:20,400
Fighting like that on board?

457
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:22,360
We're gonna get suspended.

458
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:25,320
How are we gonna find the money for Pam?

459
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,120
Right, 200,000 Baht!

460
00:22:40,520 --> 00:22:44,360
"The number you have dialed is currently unavailable."

461
00:22:44,360 --> 00:22:46,360
Why did Madam turn off her phone?

462
00:22:49,800 --> 00:22:50,800
All-New.

463
00:22:54,720 --> 00:22:57,200
What? All-New isn't answering his phone too.

464
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:58,480
Why are you calling All-New?

465
00:23:00,040 --> 00:23:02,680
That's none of your business.

466
00:23:02,680 --> 00:23:04,680
Hey, wait, where are you going?

467
00:23:08,640 --> 00:23:09,640
Understood.

468
00:23:11,040 --> 00:23:13,400
Oh, that won't be a problem.

469
00:23:13,400 --> 00:23:14,400
What's wrong?

470
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:17,240
Why are you avoiding Chai?

471
00:23:17,240 --> 00:23:19,080
I can't help you...

472
00:23:19,080 --> 00:23:21,080
if you don't tell me what's going on.

473
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:23,680
Chai.

474
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:26,120
Ah, okay. Three days, it is.

475
00:23:26,120 --> 00:23:27,960
Why are you saying hi to him?

476
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:29,960
So we can have a meal altogether.

477
00:23:32,680 --> 00:23:33,680
Are you eating alone?

478
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:35,720
I'm with Kreetha.

479
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:37,840
Oh!

480
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,680
I didn't see you there.

481
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,440
Kreetha!

482
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:47,560
I got a surprise for you.

483
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:50,000
Hang on.

484
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:51,880
It's right here.

485
00:23:55,520 --> 00:23:56,520
Here.

486
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:01,720
This is really tasty. Have a bite.

487
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:03,720
I swear, one bite and you'll be in heaven.

488
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:08,560
In heaven?

489
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,200
It's alright.

490
00:24:11,800 --> 00:24:12,800
It's okay.

491
00:24:13,280 --> 00:24:14,280
Why are you not eating it?

492
00:24:14,280 --> 00:24:15,960
I'm gonna have it. I wanna go to heaven.

493
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:16,960
Hey, hey!

494
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,200
That's Kreetha's.

495
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:19,360
Here.

496
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:20,840
Have a bite.

497
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:23,840
Will you excuse me?

498
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:31,080
What's wrong with him?

499
00:24:31,360 --> 00:24:32,360
He's afraid of chocolate?

500
00:24:33,560 --> 00:24:34,640
I think...

501
00:24:34,640 --> 00:24:38,600
Kreetha is hiding something from us.

502
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:42,720
But I think...

503
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:45,800
you’re just paying a little too much attention to him.

504
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:49,480
Got a crush on him or something?

505
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:52,600
And what about you, huh? You keep staring at me like that...

506
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:55,760
got a little crush on me, maybe?

507
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:57,760
Eww. Gross.

508
00:25:03,280 --> 00:25:05,000
Hey, there’s no way I have that kind of money.

509
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:06,120
Who the hell has 200K just lying around?

510
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,640
I’m totally broke this month.

511
00:25:07,640 --> 00:25:10,680
Two hundred thousand is a lot, man.

512
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:12,680
And Pam is crazy scary.

513
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:18,280
Excuse me, I heard that...

514
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:20,440
you two owe that psycho Pam Pam some money?

515
00:25:20,440 --> 00:25:22,440
Er...that's right.

516
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:26,320
How much?

517
00:25:26,320 --> 00:25:29,720
Not that much.

518
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:31,320
I'm asking you how much!

519
00:25:31,320 --> 00:25:32,760
200,000 each.

520
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:34,760
And we got one day to pay her back.

521
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:37,200
That's right.

522
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:38,200
I'll cover it for you.

523
00:25:39,920 --> 00:25:40,440
Oh.

524
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:43,280
But you two must promise me...

525
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:46,320
you'll help me slap that Pam Pam.

526
00:25:49,080 --> 00:25:51,080
You have five minutes to decide.

527
00:25:53,960 --> 00:25:54,960
Sky.

528
00:25:56,400 --> 00:25:57,640
I think it's a good idea.

529
00:25:57,640 --> 00:25:59,200
It's an easy job.

530
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:02,720
But if passengers fight on the plane, we could get suspended!

531
00:26:02,720 --> 00:26:05,680
But think about it...

532
00:26:05,680 --> 00:26:07,280
Suspension is temporary.

533
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,600
And if we don't take this job,

534
00:26:08,600 --> 00:26:10,000
we'll get suspended...

535
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:13,080
and we won't have any money.

536
00:26:13,080 --> 00:26:14,880
Alright, alright.

537
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:16,080
Hey!

538
00:26:16,080 --> 00:26:17,080
Let's go.

539
00:26:19,760 --> 00:26:21,400
You!

540
00:26:21,400 --> 00:26:23,800
Having trouble remembering people’s names?

541
00:26:23,800 --> 00:26:25,280
Alright.

542
00:26:25,280 --> 00:26:25,960
Bitch, Porn.

543
00:26:25,960 --> 00:26:26,960
The name is Pam.

544
00:26:27,520 --> 00:26:28,520
I've brought you this.

545
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:33,960
Cracked heel cream.

546
00:26:34,240 --> 00:26:36,840
It's for your face.

547
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:38,840
in case you crack it today when you get slapped.

548
00:26:45,040 --> 00:26:46,040
Is that so?

549
00:26:46,160 --> 00:26:48,280
Honestly, you’re lucky...

550
00:26:48,280 --> 00:26:49,880
to even be on this flight.

551
00:26:49,880 --> 00:26:53,880
You're what we call... economy class spirit, first-class delusion.

552
00:26:54,840 --> 00:26:55,840
Is that so?

553
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,040
And just because you’ve had access to running water...

554
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:02,040
doesn’t mean you’re suddenly high society.

555
00:27:02,880 --> 00:27:03,880
Is that so?

556
00:27:04,280 --> 00:27:05,720
Why do you keep saying "Is that so?"

557
00:27:05,720 --> 00:27:07,280
Oh, I get it.

558
00:27:07,280 --> 00:27:09,520
You’ve got nothing else to say, huh?

559
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:12,720
Of course. You’ve got the looks, sure...

560
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:14,920
but that’s all you’ve got.

561
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:17,480
Is that so?

562
00:27:17,920 --> 00:27:19,840
Wow, is that the only phrase you know?

563
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:23,280
My mother once taught me...

564
00:27:23,280 --> 00:27:27,280
When you want to call someone a lying snake…

565
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:29,280
just say, "Is that so?"

566
00:27:32,080 --> 00:27:33,600
If I were just a bit lower than you right now,

567
00:27:33,600 --> 00:27:35,760
I’d slap you to the floor right here in front of everyone,

568
00:27:35,760 --> 00:27:39,760
then yank you up by your hair. And let the whole plane witness your shamelessness.

569
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:44,160
Keep that pride of yours, honey.

570
00:27:44,160 --> 00:27:46,880
Tell your family about it.

571
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:48,880
Maybe they’ll be proud of you.

572
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:51,520
Oh my god.

573
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:53,520
That was all improvisation and unscripted!

574
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:55,600
What a smartmouth!

575
00:27:56,840 --> 00:27:58,760
All passengers, please remain seated.

576
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:00,640
And fasten your seatbelts, for you own safety.

577
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:02,640
Please go back to your seat.

578
00:28:05,400 --> 00:28:06,400
And fasten your seatbelt.

579
00:28:08,560 --> 00:28:09,440
How was I?

580
00:28:09,440 --> 00:28:10,440
You were awesome!

581
00:28:31,880 --> 00:28:34,240
All-New, can you hear me?

582
00:28:34,240 --> 00:28:35,480
Yeah, what's up?

583
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:36,680
Listen to me.

584
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:38,800
You, stay right where you are and don't come back.

585
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:41,520
Huh? Why? What happened?

586
00:28:41,520 --> 00:28:42,840
Glam put out a hit on us.

587
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,240
We won't make it.

588
00:28:44,240 --> 00:28:45,920
What? Really?

589
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:47,080
If anything comes up,

590
00:28:47,080 --> 00:28:48,200
I'll let you know.

591
00:28:48,200 --> 00:28:49,200
You, just stay there for now.

592
00:28:50,560 --> 00:28:51,560
What?

593
00:28:54,360 --> 00:28:55,360
The battery is dead.

594
00:29:07,840 --> 00:29:09,840
Why is the door making that weird noise?

595
00:29:13,520 --> 00:29:15,480
Ouch, that's enough.

596
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:16,360
Kreetha!

597
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:19,120
Oh, Tid-Gift.

598
00:29:21,040 --> 00:29:24,360
Hey, what exactly are you up to?

599
00:29:24,360 --> 00:29:25,640
What? What am I up to?

600
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:28,200
I saw you eavesdropping on Chai.

601
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:31,480
And after that, you've been acting shady.

602
00:29:31,480 --> 00:29:34,560
What are you hiding? Why are you avoiding him?

603
00:29:34,560 --> 00:29:35,560
Tell me now!

604
00:29:38,520 --> 00:29:39,760
Well, I'm running away...

605
00:29:39,760 --> 00:29:40,760
Running away from what?

606
00:29:42,520 --> 00:29:43,520
I can't tell you that.

607
00:29:44,480 --> 00:29:46,200
If you knew,

608
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:48,200
you'd be on a hit list too.

609
00:29:50,120 --> 00:29:51,120
A hit list?

610
00:30:00,000 --> 00:30:02,680
The seatbelt sign is off. Ready to roll?

611
00:30:02,680 --> 00:30:06,360
I’ve been holding this grudge for over twenty years.

612
00:30:06,360 --> 00:30:09,360
Now, it's my time.

613
00:30:13,120 --> 00:30:14,120
You got this, Miss Keerati.

614
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:18,760
When you die…

615
00:30:18,760 --> 00:30:21,800
don’t donate your body to science, okay?

616
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:25,800
You’ll just confuse the med students because you clearly have no brain.

617
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:31,600
Ever since the Animal Protection Act got passed,

618
00:30:31,600 --> 00:30:33,600
some dogs bark a lot more.

619
00:30:35,280 --> 00:30:37,760
And clearly, it’s not just one.

620
00:30:37,760 --> 00:30:38,920
From the looks of it...

621
00:30:38,920 --> 00:30:40,920
I see three right now.

622
00:30:43,160 --> 00:30:44,520
That mouth of yours…

623
00:30:44,520 --> 00:30:46,320
deserves a slap so hard it drowns in its own blood.

624
00:30:46,320 --> 00:30:47,320
Go for it.

625
00:30:47,320 --> 00:30:49,320
My hands have been itching.

626
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:51,880
Did you just slap me?

627
00:30:51,880 --> 00:30:52,880
No, she slapped me.

628
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:57,760
Please, please, I'm begging you.

629
00:31:09,400 --> 00:31:10,960
All passengers...

630
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:13,400
We are now descending.

631
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:15,640
Please remain seated.

632
00:31:15,640 --> 00:31:17,880
Oh, please...

633
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:19,640
calm down.

634
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:21,640
See you when we land.

635
00:31:24,480 --> 00:31:25,480
Have a seat, Madam.

636
00:31:29,120 --> 00:31:30,280
Did I do well earlier?

637
00:31:30,280 --> 00:31:32,280
You did awesome!

638
00:31:34,640 --> 00:31:35,640
Fasten your seatbelt first.

639
00:31:44,720 --> 00:31:47,320
Tell me right now, what exactly are you planning?

640
00:31:47,320 --> 00:31:48,520
It’s nothing, really. Chill.

641
00:31:48,520 --> 00:31:50,400
Don't lie to me. I know you're up to something.

642
00:31:50,400 --> 00:31:52,400
Er...Tid-Gift, you're bleeding.

643
00:31:55,360 --> 00:31:57,360
Right, I know that.

644
00:31:58,360 --> 00:31:59,360
Lift your chin a bit.

645
00:32:19,160 --> 00:32:20,040
Kreetha.

646
00:32:20,040 --> 00:32:21,040
Yes?

647
00:32:21,760 --> 00:32:22,760
Where did you get this?

648
00:32:23,640 --> 00:32:24,640
There.

649
00:32:25,200 --> 00:32:26,200
Hey!

650
00:32:26,200 --> 00:32:27,200
Is this a rag?

651
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,240
I don't know about that.

652
00:32:28,880 --> 00:32:31,600
I knew it! That's why it's stinky.

653
00:32:31,600 --> 00:32:33,600
I almost let my guard down because of you!

654
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:35,920
Tell me now!

655
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:38,880
What are you trying to do?

656
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:43,160
Hey! Tid-Gift! Are you alright?

657
00:32:43,640 --> 00:32:46,400
I don't know, I feel kinda dizzy.

658
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:47,400
Maybe the door smacked my face earlier.

659
00:33:01,720 --> 00:33:02,720
You're doomed!

660
00:33:03,560 --> 00:33:05,480
Shit, Chai!

661
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:07,120
Chai!

662
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:08,760
Chai! Hey, the door's locked?

663
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:11,200
Help! Chai!

664
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:12,600
Chai!

665
00:33:12,600 --> 00:33:13,600
Chai! Help us!

666
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:24,440
Hey, where did Pam go?

667
00:33:24,440 --> 00:33:26,480
Don't tell me she ran home already.

668
00:33:26,480 --> 00:33:30,480
Er...I think...would it be better if you transfered us the money first?

669
00:33:31,320 --> 00:33:35,320
I'll do it when I get to slap Pam Pam.

670
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:39,720
Alright, we'll help you look for her.

671
00:33:39,720 --> 00:33:40,720
That way!

672
00:33:51,360 --> 00:33:54,240
Maybe Keerati chickened out and ran home?

673
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:57,160
There's no way. She never gave up.

674
00:33:57,160 --> 00:33:59,200
She'd never run home.

675
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:00,200
Go that way!

676
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:10,880
Why do I smell enemy nearby?

677
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:13,240
Why can't I find her? Where did she go?

678
00:34:13,240 --> 00:34:14,240
Did she go that way?

679
00:34:14,800 --> 00:34:15,800
Why are you walking ahead of me?

680
00:34:16,640 --> 00:34:19,640
Help! Help!

681
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:27,240
Are you going to tell me now what you're up to?

682
00:34:27,240 --> 00:34:29,520
Since there's no way out of this now,

683
00:34:29,520 --> 00:34:32,480
I'll tell you the truth.

684
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,480
I'm here to find info on Mr. Glam.

685
00:34:36,400 --> 00:34:38,400
And I think he probably knows who I am now.

686
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:43,400
Tid-Gift!

687
00:35:03,800 --> 00:35:04,800
I swear, I think she’s hiding in that shop.

688
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:12,640
Where is she?

689
00:35:34,360 --> 00:35:35,360
This airport is so big.

690
00:35:35,840 --> 00:35:36,840
Will I find her?

691
00:35:37,160 --> 00:35:38,160
Where could she be?

692
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:39,240
We haven't slapped her yet.

693
00:35:39,560 --> 00:35:40,560
But this is tiring.

694
00:35:42,160 --> 00:35:42,840
Pam...

695
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:44,760
Where? Help me find her.

696
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:45,760
She must be around here somewhere.

697
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:55,000
Are we in a maze or something?

698
00:35:55,680 --> 00:35:59,480
Well, you challenged her to a slap battle without setting the location!

699
00:35:59,480 --> 00:36:00,480
Will we find her?

700
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:03,240
Let's go home. This is a waste of time.

701
00:36:03,240 --> 00:36:04,240
Let me check a bit more.

702
00:36:26,240 --> 00:36:27,240
Okay, let's go.

703
00:36:28,480 --> 00:36:29,480
Let's go home.

704
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:43,400
Mr. Chai.

705
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:46,240
I think Tid-Gift hasn't gone home yet.

706
00:36:46,240 --> 00:36:48,240
Her phone is still here.

707
00:36:50,200 --> 00:36:51,200
Have you looked all over the place?

708
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:52,720
Yes.

709
00:36:52,960 --> 00:36:53,920
You couldn't find her?

710
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:54,920
No.

711
00:36:57,680 --> 00:36:58,680
Hey!

712
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:03,720
Hey, Tid-Gift! Kreetha!

713
00:37:11,720 --> 00:37:12,720
Easy, easy.

714
00:37:14,280 --> 00:37:15,280
Sit here.

715
00:37:19,400 --> 00:37:20,400
Are you okay?

716
00:37:22,360 --> 00:37:23,360
I'm so sorry.

717
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:26,240
I didn't know you guys were in there.

718
00:37:26,240 --> 00:37:29,120
If I'd known, I wouldn't have locked you up in there.

719
00:37:29,120 --> 00:37:34,960
I'm afraid someone might walk in when the room's being sprayed.

720
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:38,960
Wait, what about when you said you were gonna kill someone?

721
00:37:40,320 --> 00:37:41,480
Kill mosquitoes!

722
00:37:41,480 --> 00:37:42,360
What?

723
00:37:42,360 --> 00:37:44,400
Come on, I wouldn’t kill a person.

724
00:37:44,400 --> 00:37:46,480
I’m just following orders from Mr. Glam to spray mosquito repellent...

725
00:37:46,480 --> 00:37:48,480
all over the office...

726
00:37:49,160 --> 00:37:50,160
Oh, I see.

727
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:51,240
Right, Kreetha...

728
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:53,920
Anyway, what were we just talking about earlier?

729
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:57,680
I totally blacked out. Can’t remember a thing.

730
00:37:57,680 --> 00:37:59,680
You really don’t remember?

731
00:38:03,480 --> 00:38:05,480
Good. Let’s keep it that way.

732
00:38:07,360 --> 00:38:10,440
But why were you two even in there?

733
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:13,200
Didn’t you know they were gonna be spraying?

734
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:15,400
I posted it in the group chat.

735
00:38:16,320 --> 00:38:18,400
I didn’t see any announcement.

736
00:38:18,400 --> 00:38:20,800
Wait, don’t tell me you’re not even in the group?

737
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,000
Nope. I’m not.

738
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:25,000
What? Tid-Gift, you’re in the group, why didn’t you know?

739
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:27,880
My phone’s charging. I didn’t check.

740
00:38:27,880 --> 00:38:29,040
How about this?

741
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:32,080
I’ll add you to the group, cool?

742
00:38:32,080 --> 00:38:33,240
Everyone’s in there.

743
00:38:33,240 --> 00:38:36,560
Me, Mr. Glam...

744
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:39,400
So if anything comes up, we can all talk directly.

745
00:38:39,400 --> 00:38:41,760
Thanks a lot, Chai.

746
00:38:41,760 --> 00:38:45,480
If you need to send pics, videos, anything, just drop them in the chat.

747
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:46,520
I'll look forward to them.

748
00:38:46,520 --> 00:38:48,680
That's sneaky, Chai.

749
00:38:48,680 --> 00:38:51,440
Come on, let’s go sit on the couch or something.

750
00:38:51,840 --> 00:38:52,640
Yeah, let's do that.

751
00:38:52,640 --> 00:38:53,640
Excuse me.

752
00:38:54,280 --> 00:38:55,080
C'mon.

753
00:38:55,080 --> 00:38:56,080
Okay.

754
00:38:59,880 --> 00:39:01,240
Siri.

755
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:04,240
Blacklist that Keerati woman right now.

756
00:39:04,240 --> 00:39:06,320
Isn’t that a little personal, Madam?

757
00:39:06,320 --> 00:39:09,480
Or do you want to get ambushed and slapped again, huh?

758
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:13,480
As for Sky and Chaba, they got away this time.

759
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:18,560
The money they owe me? Let it be.

760
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:21,880
So I can collect some favors later.

761
00:39:21,880 --> 00:39:24,680
Madam, I got something juicy.

762
00:39:24,680 --> 00:39:27,880
If it’s not actually juicy, I’ll take your head off instead.

763
00:39:27,880 --> 00:39:29,760
A group chat, Madam.

764
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:31,840
Mr. Glam’s in it.

765
00:39:31,840 --> 00:39:34,560
Chai added me in already.

766
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:35,560
Let me see.

767
00:39:41,600 --> 00:39:44,720
Wait, using a profile picture like this?

768
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,720
How are we supposed to know what his face looks like?

769
00:39:48,640 --> 00:39:49,640
Still, good job, Kreetha.

770
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:54,160
If All-New comes back, we’ll probably get more info.

771
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:55,160
Yes, Madam.

772
00:39:55,240 --> 00:39:58,240
Here, message him.

773
00:39:58,480 --> 00:39:59,480
Text Glam.

774
00:40:00,720 --> 00:40:02,240
Is that really a good idea, Madam?

775
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:05,920
It’s fine, just say something like “Hi” or whatever.

776
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:08,080
That’s what every newbie does.

777
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:09,040
Just message him.

778
00:40:09,040 --> 00:40:10,040
Yes, ma’am.

779
00:40:19,240 --> 00:40:20,240
Someone's read it already.

780
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:27,200
“Happy Thursday.”

781
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:29,000
Here.

782
00:40:31,680 --> 00:40:35,680
I’m telling you, Mr. Glam has to be over fifty for sure.

783
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:38,480
We’ll have All-New check.

784
00:40:41,280 --> 00:40:45,280
But today, seriously, thank you so much.

785
00:40:45,320 --> 00:40:50,320
You helped us get one step closer to Glam.

786
00:40:51,480 --> 00:40:55,520
I prayed to the zebra shrine since this morning.

787
00:40:57,040 --> 00:40:59,560
And wow, it worked instantly.

788
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:02,200
What about me, Madam?

789
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:02,960
What?

790
00:41:02,960 --> 00:41:04,560
I went and found the info!

791
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:08,560
Well, I already said you did great. What more do you want?

792
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:11,080
Siri, I think...

793
00:41:11,080 --> 00:41:13,520
the zebra shrine has to be bigger than this.

794
00:41:13,520 --> 00:41:15,520
Oh, totally, Madam.

795
00:41:16,080 --> 00:41:20,080
I’ll feed him well till he’s chubby and happy.

796
00:41:20,080 --> 00:41:21,080
Sadhu.

797
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:49,080
Shit. Mr. Glam again.

798
00:41:59,080 --> 00:42:00,680
Why does he say good morning every damn day?

799
00:42:00,680 --> 00:42:02,680
Ugh. Totally useless.

800
00:42:17,480 --> 00:42:18,440
Hey, bitch, Porn.

801
00:42:18,440 --> 00:42:21,800
Having trouble remembering people’s names?

802
00:42:21,800 --> 00:42:23,200
Alright.

803
00:42:23,200 --> 00:42:24,080
Pam Pam.

804
00:42:24,080 --> 00:42:25,600
My name is Porn.

805
00:42:25,600 --> 00:42:26,600
It's Pam!

806
00:42:30,040 --> 00:42:31,040
Oh, sorry.

807
00:42:31,800 --> 00:42:33,480
If you can’t pay me back in time,

808
00:42:33,480 --> 00:42:36,240
I’ll report you to the DP...

809
00:42:36,240 --> 00:42:38,680
D...

810
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:41,800
CA...

811
00:42:41,800 --> 00:42:43,080
The what now?

812
00:42:43,080 --> 00:42:43,920
DP...

813
00:42:43,920 --> 00:42:45,200
DPDC...

814
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,600
DPDCA.

815
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:47,360
Okay, cut!

816
00:42:47,360 --> 00:42:48,800
You're so good. How could you remember those lines?

817
00:42:49,400 --> 00:42:50,400
It's a wrap!

818
00:42:51,560 --> 00:42:52,640
Thank you so much!

819
00:42:52,640 --> 00:42:53,640
You're so good at memorizing lines!

820
00:42:55,680 --> 00:42:58,080
Mint. Mint. Mint!

821
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,000
I'll get you some water.

822
00:43:00,640 --> 00:43:01,640
Mint!

823
00:43:02,560 --> 00:43:03,040
Huh?

824
00:43:03,040 --> 00:43:04,760
Scratch your head.

825
00:43:04,760 --> 00:43:06,760
Yeah, keep doing that.

826
00:43:07,920 --> 00:43:09,920
Get it out of your hair.

827
00:43:15,120 --> 00:43:16,640
I've never had lice in my life!

828
00:43:18,600 --> 00:43:20,600
You were so great. Ten out of ten.

829
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:30,440
Okay, cut!

830
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:32,040
Look what you made me do.

831
00:43:33,960 --> 00:43:34,560
That was fantastic!

832
00:43:34,560 --> 00:43:35,560
Is she over there?

833
00:43:38,240 --> 00:43:39,240
No.

834
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:40,920
She's not here either.

835
00:43:42,600 --> 00:43:43,600
One more time.

836
00:43:48,160 --> 00:43:49,160
The other way around...

837
00:43:52,360 --> 00:43:53,360
Cut!

838
00:43:53,600 --> 00:43:54,600
I'm dizzy.

839
00:43:55,240 --> 00:43:56,240
What have we done to them?

840
00:43:56,680 --> 00:43:57,680
I'm so dizzy.

841
00:44:00,960 --> 00:44:02,360
If I were just a bit higher than you right now,

842
00:44:02,360 --> 00:44:04,400
I’d slap you to the floor right here...

843
00:44:04,400 --> 00:44:05,360
What is it?

844
00:44:05,360 --> 00:44:06,600
If I were just a bit lower than you right now,

845
00:44:06,600 --> 00:44:08,160
I’d slap you to the floor right here in front of everyone...

846
00:44:08,160 --> 00:44:09,320
If I were just a bit lower than you right now,

847
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:11,040
I’d slap you to the floor...

848
00:44:11,040 --> 00:44:12,800
and then what?

849
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:13,240
Help me!

850
00:44:14,200 --> 00:44:14,720
This is so difficult.

851
00:44:14,720 --> 00:44:16,200
If I were just a bit lower than you right now,

852
00:44:16,200 --> 00:44:18,240
I’d slap you to the floor right here in front of everyone...

853
00:44:18,240 --> 00:44:19,600
If I were...

854
00:44:19,600 --> 00:44:21,760
If I were just a bit lower than you right now,

855
00:44:21,760 --> 00:44:24,200
I’d slap you to the floor right here...

856
00:44:24,200 --> 00:44:24,720
in front of everyone.

857
00:44:25,080 --> 00:44:26,080
in front of everyone.

858
00:44:26,240 --> 00:44:28,640
then yank you up by your hair.

859
00:44:28,640 --> 00:44:32,360
And let the whole plane witness your shamelessness.

860
00:44:32,360 --> 00:44:33,080
That's right!

861
00:44:33,080 --> 00:44:34,080
This is so hard!

862
00:44:34,840 --> 00:44:36,520
You guys better go quickly.

863
00:44:36,520 --> 00:44:39,280
Don’t forget, this flight’s pilot is Peck.

864
00:44:39,280 --> 00:44:40,160
Peck.

865
00:44:40,160 --> 00:44:41,160
Who's that?

866
00:44:41,360 --> 00:44:44,760
Peck is the pilot who always invites the crew out for drinks after the flight.

867
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:45,360
All-New.

868
00:44:45,360 --> 00:44:47,120
I met a flight crew named Peck.

869
00:44:47,120 --> 00:44:48,560
She knows Mr. Glam.

870
00:44:48,560 --> 00:44:49,560
Find out about it!

871
00:44:49,760 --> 00:44:51,400
This is the King's bottle game.

872
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:52,680
I order you to...

873
00:44:52,680 --> 00:44:54,680
give the person next to you some smooches.

874
00:44:57,040 --> 00:44:58,360
This is such a good game.

875
00:44:58,360 --> 00:44:59,600
Hey!

876
00:44:59,600 --> 00:45:00,120
What are you doing?

877
00:45:02,520 --> 00:45:04,520
Kreetha's dead.
